"a.饿极了的，贪婪的 【英】 adj.饿极了的，贪婪 的(rapacious; hungry) 【考】 incontrovertible : disputed / untenable : defended / ravenous : satisfied(无可争议的无法争议 /不可守卫的无法防卫 /十分贪婪的无法满足) 【记】 来自raven(掠夺)＋ou s 【例】 The ravenous student ate a whole pizza. adj. 饿极了的, 贪婪的 【记】源于: raven(n /v 掠夺), ous多－掠夺很多－饿极了的, 贪婪的 【类】incontrovertible: disputed = untenable: defended = 『ravenous: satisfied』无可争议的无法被争议 = 不可守卫的无法被防卫 = 『十分贪婪的无法被满足』 【记】v=f=ph=p, 与rape (掠夺)相近，狼掠夺食物时是饿极了的；音：肉无饿死，没肉吃饿的要死， 【相关】raven 大乌鸦, 掠夺, 狼吞虎咽，rapacious 掠夺的, 贪婪的, ravin 捕食, 掠夺, 猎食 ravenous (adj.)  late 14c., ""obsessed with plundering, extremely greedy,"" from Old French ravinos, of people, ""rapacious, violent,"" of water, ""swift-flowing,"" from raviner ""to seize,"" from ravine ""violent rush, robbery"" (see ravine). Meaning ""voracious, very hungry"" is from early 15c. Related: Ravenously; ravenousness."
